Prosper Loan Dataset Investigation¶

Analysis done by: Zahra Al-Hourani¶

Investigation Overview¶

The main interest is to figure out What factors affect a borrower Rate, borrower APR, Loan Status.

Dataset Overview¶

This dataset is financial and related to the Loan, Borrowers, Lenders, Interest rates, etc. Prosper or Prosper Marketplace Inc. is a San Francisco, California-based company specializing in loans at low-interest rates to borrowers. In this dataset, we are using the data from Prosper to analyze it and trying to find the pattern in the Prosper data.

The dataset is comprised of 81 variables and contains 113937 entries.

Correlation Map¶

Through this map, I noticed a very strong relationship between:¶

  • 'BorrowerAPR and LenderYield' have a very strong relationship = 0.99, The higher the Annual Percentage Rate the higher the lenderYield 'the interest rate on the loan'.

  • BorrowerRate and BorrowerAPR have a very strong relationship with these variables:

    • EstimatedEffectiveYield
    • EstimatedLoss
    • EstimatedReturn
Sometimes a negative correlation is logical and meaningful, I noticed from the previous chart some negative values that are meaningful. Like:¶
  • 'BorrowerAPR and ProsperScore' have a negative correlation,The lower ProsperScor, leads to an increase in risks, and therefore interest rates will increase.
  • 'LenderYield and ProsperScore' have a negative correlation, The higher ProsperScor, the interest rate will decrease, and therefore the return on the lender will decrease.
  • The box plot shows that there is an indications that 'Prosperscore' is a good factor to determine the 'BorrowersAPR'. the lower ProsperScor, This leads to an increase in risks, and therefore interest rates will increase.
  • 'LenderYield and ProsperScore' have a negative correlation, The higher ProsperScor, the interest rate will decrease, and therefore the return on the lender will decrease.

  • The scatter chart shows a strong relationship between 'BorrowerRate' and 'LenderYield' which means The higher Rate the higher the lenderYield 'the interest rate on the loan'.

  • High 'EstimatedReturn' repeated with the positive correlation between the 'LenderYield' and 'BorrowerRate'.
